laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 9-10 mm and fluid-filled with mucosal hyperenhancement, periappendiceal edema is noted. No rim-enhancing fluid collection or regions of mucosal nonenhancement. No free air. Normal small and large bowel in course and caliber without obstruction. No enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes. A small amount of free fluid in the pelvis is within the physiologic range.
